# Testing

- Every public behaviour gets a unit test (Vitest + happy-dom) in
  `tests/unit/`: schema validation, each adapter, data-source precedence,
  events, registration guard, fail-safe behaviour on bad data.
- Accessibility is verified with axe-core via Playwright in `tests/a11y/` —
  assertions must require **zero** violations.
- User-facing flows (render, keyboard navigation, activation, container
  resize) are covered with Playwright in `tests/e2e/`.
- Visual baselines for the rendered component live in `tests/visual/`;
  regenerate intentionally with `--update-snapshots`, never casually.
- Tests must be deterministic: no real network, no timing races; use
  fixtures under `tests/unit/fixtures/`.
